The EFF holds a memorial service for late Zimbabwean president Robert Mugabe JOHANNESBURG - The EFF will hold a memorial service for the late Zimbabwean president Robert Mugabe on Thursday. EFF president, Julius Malema will be the main speaker at the memorial held at theÂ Orlando East Communal Hall. The 95-year-old statesman died in a Singapore hospital on last week. His remains arrived back in the country from Singapore on Wednesday.